==Korean==
===Noun===
'''허벅다리''' (heobeog-dari, heobeok-)
# [[thigh]], cf. [[thick]] (of the [[calf]], [[arm]], [[palm]], [[thumb]], etc.), German [[Dickbein]] "thigh",  literally, "thick leg". (The [[thigh]] is, so to speak, the [[thick]] of the leg, the thickest of all thicks; both appear cognate with each other and with [[dike]], [[dough]], etc. as well. Such is exactly the case with [[팔뚝]] (pal-ttug, -ttuk), literally, "arm-thick".)   

====Synonyms====
* [[넓적다리]] (neolbjeog-dari, neolpjeok-) literally, [[large]] [[leg]]
* [[대퇴]] ([[大腿]], daetoe) literally, [[big]] [[leg]]

====Antonyms====
* [[아래|아랫]]다리 (araes-dari, araet-) literally, [[lower]] [[leg]] (below the knee)
* [[소퇴]] ([[小腿]], sotoe) literally, [[small]] [[leg]]

====Related terms====
* [[궁둥이]] (gungdungI) [[hip]]
* [[다리]] (dari) [[leg]]
* [[무릎]] (mureup) [[lap]], literally, [[knee]] 
* [[장딴지]] (jangttanji) [[calf]]
* [[정강이]] (jeonggangI) [[shank]], [[shin]]
* [[종아리]] (jongAri) [[calf]]
* [[허벅지]] (heobeog-ji, heobeok-) the inside of the [[thigh]]

====See also====
* [[두께]] (dukke) [[thick]]ness, cf. German [[Dicke]]
* [[둑]] (dug, duk) [[dike]]
* [[떡]] (tteog, tteok) [[dough]] (Korean food) 
* [[팔뚝]] (pal-ttug, -ttuk) [[forearm]], literally, "the [[thick]] of the arm"  
* [[팔목]] (pal-mog, -mok) [[wrist]], literally, "the [[neck]] of the arm"

